1.  [Create the web app]{.Emphasis}

    In this step you create the web app for
    {% $sca-project-variables.GoogleCloud %}.

    1.  In
        {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %},
        go to the Introduction page.

        In the
        {% $cc_C_CyberArk.CompanyName %}
        Admin portal, select [Cloud connectivity \> Configure cloud
        provider apps]{.Emphasis}.

    2.  In the second tile, click [+ Create a web app]{.Emphasis}.

    3.  In the dialog box that opens click
        {% $sca-project-variables.GoogleCloud %},
        and click [Next]{.Emphasis}.

    4.  Select the
        {% $sca-project-variables.GoogleCloud %}
        organization, and click [Continue]{.Emphasis}.

        ::: note
        - It may take some time for the organizations to display.

        - If your organization doesn\'t appear, this means that it
          hasn\'t been onboarded to
          {% $cc_product_vars.CEM-short %}.
          For details about onboarding the organization, see
          `<xref href="../CloudAdmin/cv-gcp-discovery.htm#Discover">`{=html}Add
          a new Google Cloud organization`</xref>`{=html}.
        :::

    5.  If you are working with
        {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
        as your external IdP, select [Use
        {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
        as an external IdP]{.Emphasis}

    6.  Click [Create]{.Emphasis}.

        `<snippetblock src="SCA-snippets/asynch-discovery-in-background.flsnp">`{=html}`</snippetblock>`{=html}

