Tab 2 Content -Identity Admin

This section describes how to use
{% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}
to create a web app in
{% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
for your GCP project.

::: tip
You can also create web apps in
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
where you provide only the minimum details and
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
provides all the rest of the details. See
`<xref href="#Configur">`{=html}Add a Google Cloud web
app`</xref>`{=html}.
:::

1.  [Add a web app for the Google Cloud console]{.Emphasis}

    1.  Sign in to
        {% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}.

    2.  Go to [Apps & Widgets]{.Emphasis} \> [Web Apps]{.Emphasis} and
        click [Add Web Apps]{.Emphasis} above the grid.

    3.  In the [Search]{.Emphasis} tab, type [Google]{.Emphasis} and add
        the [Google Cloud Platform]{.Emphasis} application.

    4.  Click [Yes]{.Emphasis} to confirm you want to add the
        application and then close the [Add Web Apps]{.Emphasis} wizard.
        The app settings page opens.

2.  [Specify your Google Cloud settings]{.Emphasis}

    In this step you configure the web app with your
    {% $sca-project-variables.GoogleCloud %}
    settings.

    1.  In the
        {% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}[Web
        Apps ]{.Emphasis}page, select the web app you want to configure.

    2.  Select the Settings tab and in the [Your Primary Domain in
        Google Cloud Platform]{.Emphasis} field, apply your primary
        domain from the Google Cloud console.

3.  [Enable Secure Cloud Access]{.Emphasis}

    In this step you enable secure access to the application with zero
    standing permissions.

    1.  In
        {% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %},
        go to [Apps & Widgets ]{.Emphasis}\> [Web Apps ]{.Emphasis}and
        click the web app you want to modify.

    2.  Click the
        [{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-full %}]{.Emphasis}
        tab and select [ Enable
        {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-full %}]{.Emphasis}.

    3.  If you want to use
        {% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
        as a third-party IdP, select
        [{% $cc_product_vars.Identity-full %}
        is the IDP]{.Emphasis}.

    ::: note
    `<snippetblock src="SCA-snippets/ready-to-deploy.flsnp">`{=html}`</snippetblock>`{=html}
    :::

4.  [Configure an identity provider (IdP)]{.Emphasis}

    `<snippetblock src="../CloudAdmin/CloudAdminSnippets/cyberark-ext-idp-google.flsnp">`{=html}`</snippetblock>`{=html}

5.  [Enable
    {% $cc_product_vars.SWS-full %}
    (Optional)]{.Emphasis}

    `<snippetblock src="SCA-snippets/enable-sws-intro.flsnp">`{=html}`</snippetblock>`{=html}
    `<snippetblock src="SCA-snippets/EnableSWS.flsnp">`{=html}`</snippetblock>`{=html}
